OL,3,CTV-related anniversaries for 20 APR
OL,4,CCHANNELS
OL,5,
OL,6,CG1964FBBC Two was expected to launch
OL,7,Fat 7.20pm. However, a serious power
OL,8,Ffailure at Battersea Power Station
OL,9,Fknocked out the power supply to BBC
OL,10,FTelevision Centre.
OL,11,
OL,12,FBBC One was kept on the air via
OL,13,Ffacilities at Alexandra Palace.
OL,14,
OL,15,FOther than occasional news updates on
OL,16,FBBC Two that evening, where presenter
OL,17,FGerald Priestland explained the power
OL,18,Fissues, no other programmes were
OL,19,Fbroadcast on BBC Two that day.
OL,20,
OL,21,FThe first official programme on BBC Two
OL,22,Fwas Play School at 11am the next day.
OL,23,Sppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppp
